==Spanish==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[iam]]''

===Adverb===
'''ya'''

# [[now]]
# [[already]]
# in the [[near]] [[future]]; [[soon]]
# [[immediately]]
# [[anymore]]; no [[longer]]
# ''[[emphatical]]''
#: ''¡'''ya''' lo se!'' - “I know!”

'''no ya'''
# not [[only]]

'''ya, pero...'''
# yes, but...

'''ya que'''
# [[since]]; now that

====Synonyms====
*[[ahora]] (1)
*[[ahorita]] (1, ''colloquial'')
*[[ahora mismo]] (4)

===Conjunction===
'''ya ... ya'''

# [[first]] ''this'' [[then]] ''that''
#: ''¡'''ya''' lluvia '''ya''' nieve!'' - “first rain now snow!”
# [[whether]] ''this'' [[or]] ''that''
#: '''''ya''' sol '''ya''' lluvia'' - “whether sun or rain”

